author: rhuijben
msg: When introducing file externals in a workingcopy use the 'not-present' state
instead of 'added' to remove an unexpected/unneeded transient state. A
not-present switched node will automatically bring in the right node on
updating and doesn't need special casing in the update editor.
This also updates the notification of incoming externals to the normal 'A',
where it used to show 'E' for existing.
* subversion/libsvn_client/externals.c
(switch_file_external): Remove all error recovery code because with a not-
present marker there is nothing to recover. Don't create an empty file but
do check for existing nodes.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/adm_ops.c
(svn_wc__register_file_external): Don't create a local addition, because we
don't need this registration and it only makes things harder on the update
editor.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/update_editor.c
(merge_file): Remove special condition for bringing in file externals via the
add state. Update expected statee for file externals to be just normal and
not-present.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/externals_tests.py
(binary_file_externals, update_lose_file_external,
wc_repos_file_externals, wc_repos_file_externals):
Expect 'A' status for incoming file externals, just like other
nodes (and externals) that are checked out.
